    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Despite the Not Accepted COU-level determination, the credibility assessment package itself is formally accepted as a complete and valid evidence record per the V&V 40 process. All 13 credibility factors have been evaluated or explicitly flagged as epistemic gaps. The assessment correctly documents that achieved levels fall below required levels across all assessed factors at Model Risk Level 5. The evidence package, including the Monte Carlo UQ results and the multi-operating-point validation data described in the hemolysis modelling literature (see referenced publication), is accepted as a faithful representation of the current model credibility state for regulatory submission purposes.",
